parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic or at intersections.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle stalls at a stop light
the engine fails to accelerate
the forward collision warning indicator comes on repeatedly while driving with no obstacle in front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Rear Automatic Braking (RAB) and Parking Sensor System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning RAB and parking sensor system can cause the vehicle to fail to detect obstacles, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when reversing or parking.
symptoms: The Rear Automatic Braking (RAB) Warning Light symbol appears on the dashboard
the Parking Sensor Error warning appears on the dashboard
the parking sensors do not warn of obstructions as designed
the VDC Settings Menu illuminated light dims while accelerating and returns to normal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause various warning lights and messages to appear on the dashboard, which can be distracting and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The Master Warning Light symbol appears on the dashboard
warning messages appear on the dashboard
including "Warning Malfunction See Owner's Manual" and "Warning No Key Detected
Check Rear Seat for All Articles and Parking Sensor Off".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stall can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic or with passengers on board.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
the accelerator pedal has no effect
the vehicle is unable to move
the engine appears normal with no unusual noises or warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to brake unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The brakes are applied automatically without any apparent reason
a warning light or message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle slows down or stops suddenly without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling issue can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, increased risk of accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning
often at low speeds
such as when stopping or driving at around 25mph. The vehicle may roll backwards or remain in gear
and the collision warning
battery
and oil light indicators may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The FEB sensor malfunction can cause the vehicle to unnecessarily activate the emergency brake, leading to sudden stops, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The FEB sensor activates when there is no obstruction present
potentially causing the vehicle to suddenly stop or slow down
even when driving at full speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the AEB system can cause the vehicle to come to a grinding halt, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when there is no obstruction behind the vehicle. This can be alarming and may cause drivers to lose trust in the vehicle's safety features.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without warning
the collision alert light comes on while traveling at a steady speed
the system beeps or alerts the driver of an obstruction when there is none
the vehicle becomes difficult to maneuver or back up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Insufficient Brake and Gas Pedal Clearance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake and gas pedals can cause accidental simultaneous pressing, leading to sudden and unintended acceleration, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward unexpectedly
the driver experiences difficulty controlling the vehicle
the brake and gas pedals are easily pressed simultaneously
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver Side Door Malfunction in Cold Temperatures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the driver side door in cold temperatures can cause the door to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible for the driver to exit the vehicle, which can lead to safety risks in emergency situations.
symptoms: The driver side door will not unlock or open when the ambient air temperature is 25 degrees or below.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the hood while driving can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: The hood flies open while driving
often at high speeds
causing damage to the hood and surrounding components.
